@NODE "What" "The decoder"



MPEG2decoderPRO is a very powerful MPEG2 decoder. It can be used in any
circumstances. It has a GUI and can be used from shell.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Req" "300THz PentiumX cpu with 512 GB mem..."



A 040+, on a demand, I can recompile for a lower CPU.

Fast RAM is not requred, but recommended.

OS 2.1+ (OS 3.1 tested omly).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Dis"  "If it blows up, it's your fault"



I take no responsibility for any destruction caused by this
program. Use it at your own risk. You've been warned.

@ENDNODE

@NODE  "Ins" "You'll need a hammer"



The simplies way is to use the supplied installer script, but you can
simply copy the program whenever you want, and the saver modules in a
PROGDIR:savers/ directory. You CAN also copy the developer files to any
place on your HD.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Use" "The rules"



You can simply start the program from shell with a GUI option or from
workbench by doubleclicking the icon and enjoy it. I think the GUI is 
self explaining.


On the other hand, The shell usage is much more flexible and powerful. You
can supply the following options:


FILE,SAVE/K,SAVEF0RMAT/K,TASKPRI/N,STARTNUM/N,P0RTNAME/K,GUI/S


FILE -- an mpeg file to decode.


SAVE -- a file(s) to save the frames to, for example: "kissing%04d". The
extention must be added automatically by the saver library.


SAVEFORMAT -- a base name of a saver library, without .library extention.
The savers are allways searched in PROGDIR:savers/ directory.


TASKPRI -- you can set the task priority with this option. Default is 0.


STARTNUM -- when you decode several mpegs in a series, for example, from a
porno site, you can start the saved frames numbering from a concrete number.


PORTNAME -- This option causes the opening of a message port with the
supplied name and waiting for it, after saving each frame. This can be
used in some AREXX scripts.


GUI -- envokes a GUI.


Here is an example of a command line:


   MPEG2decoderPRO kissing.mpg SAVE=kissing%04d SAVEFORMAT=jpg


@ENDNODE

